Description: CVE-2026-33908 - Fix recursive stack exhaustion in DestroyXMLTree()
 ImageMagick frees XML tree memory via DestroyXMLTree() recursively with
 no depth limit. Deeply nested XML structures exhaust the stack, causing
 denial-of-service conditions. This patch adds a depth limit using
 MagickMaxRecursionDepth and also adds a length check after UTF16 to
 UTF8 conversion in NewXMLTree().
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/4a8819a0e1c2768d592cb6e8584cadecf9cf536e
