+# CVE-2026-28493 – Not Applicable to ImageMagick 6.x (Debian Bookworm)
+
+## Overview
+
+CVE-2026-28493 describes an out-of-bounds write vulnerability in the SIXEL image decoder caused by an `(int)` typecast overflow. The fix commit changes `(int) offset` to `(size_t) offset` in the buffer indexing expression within `coders/sixel.c`.
+
+This vulnerability is **specific to ImageMagick v7** and does not affect the v6 codebase used in Debian Bookworm.
+
+---
+
+## Why This CVE Does Not Apply
+
+The vulnerable code pattern in ImageMagick v7 (`coders/sixel.c`, line 594):
+
+```c
+imbuf[(int) offset+x] = (sixel_pixel_t) color_index;
+```
+
+The `(int)` cast truncates the `offset` value (which can exceed `INT_MAX` for large images), causing an integer overflow and out-of-bounds write.
+
+### ImageMagick 6.9.11-60 (Debian Bookworm) is NOT vulnerable because:
+
+1. **`offset` is declared as `ssize_t`** (64-bit signed integer), not `int`
+2. **No `(int)` typecast** exists in the buffer access — `imbuf[offset]` is used directly
+3. **`memset()` is used** for repeated pixel writes instead of a per-pixel loop with cast indexing
+4. **Bounds checking is already present**: `if (offset >= (imsx*imsy))` and `if ((offset+repeat_count) >= (imsx*imsy))`
+
+### Code comparison
+
+**ImageMagick v7 (VULNERABLE):**
+```c
+for (x = 0; x < repeat_count; x++)
+    imbuf[(int) offset+x] = (sixel_pixel_t) color_index;
+```
+
+**ImageMagick v6 / Debian Bookworm (NOT VULNERABLE):**
+```c
+// Single pixel write — no (int) cast
+imbuf[offset] = color_index;
+
+// Repeated write uses memset — no (int) cast
+(void) memset(imbuf + offset, color_index, repeat_count);
+```
+
+---
+
+## Verification
+
+| Check | Result |
+|-------|--------|
+| `grep '(int).*offset' coders/sixel.c` | No matches |
+| `offset` variable type | `ssize_t` (64-bit) |
+| Buffer access pattern | Direct indexing + `memset()` |
+| Bounds checking | Present before all writes |
+
+---
+
+## Affected Versions
+
+| Version | Status |
+|---------|--------|
+| ImageMagick 7.x (< 7.1.2-13) | Vulnerable |
+| ImageMagick 6.9.11-60 (Debian Bookworm) | Not vulnerable |
+| ImageMagick 6.9.x (all v6 releases) | Not vulnerable |
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- **Fix commit (v7 only):** https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/commit/6cefe972445185cbb9c76651231d52512e0ec14b
+- **Advisory:** GHSA-r39q-jr8h-gcq2
+- **Debian Security Tracker:** https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-28493
+
+## Recommendation
+
+Treat this CVE as **not applicable** for Debian Bookworm ImageMagick packages. The vulnerable code pattern (`(int)` typecast on offset) is exclusive to the v7 codebase and was never present in v6. No patch is needed.
